</div></div></div> <section class="content"><div class="story_parent"><div class="story_links story_links-vertical" > <button class="button button--share button--share-facebook st_facebook_custom" st_image=""> <img alt="Facebook" class="icon icon-facebook" src="/themes/custom/iebs/images/sharethis/facebook.svg"> </button> <button class="button button--share button--share-twitter st_twitter_custom" st_image=""> <img alt="Twitter" class="icon icon-twitter" src="/themes/custom/iebs/images/sharethis/twitter.svg"> </button> <button class="button button--share button--share-email st_email_custom" st_image=""> <img alt="Email" class="icon icon-email" src="/themes/custom/iebs/images/sharethis/email.svg"> </button> <button class="button button--share button--share-reddit st_reddit_custom" st_image=""> <img alt="Reddit" class="icon icon-reddit" src="/themes/custom/iebs/images/sharethis/reddit.svg"> </button></div></div><div class="row--article-text"><div class="field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field--item"><div><p>During his pro-wrestling&nbsp;heyday, Bruno Sammartino sold out Madison Square Garden 188 times, was named the world&rsquo;s strongest man and held the <a href="https://www.insideedition.com/media/videos/stone-cold-steve-austin-on-how-he-helped-dwayne-the-rock-johnsons-wwe-career-57595" target="_blank">WWE Championship Belt</a> for 2,803 consecutive days. Arnold Schwarzenegger called&nbsp;Bruno's life "one of the greatest immigration stories that anyone can think of."&nbsp;</p><p>But that life of triumph&nbsp;almost didn't happen. Bruno grew up in poverty in Pizzoferrato, Italy, during World War II. As a boy, he was chronically ill. When his family fled&nbsp;the Nazis for America, he faced prejudice and bullying for being an immigrant.</p><div id="mobile_incontent_ad_middle_top" data-ad="mobile_incontent_ad_middle_top" class="mobile_incontent_ad_middle_top gpt_ads"></div><script>
if (ctdBidBarrelUtility.isMobile() || (!ctdBidBarrelUtility.isMobile() && '' != '')) {
